title: Bug 110566: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When setting the filter to 'row[0] equals to 0', the dataset returns the wrong result or null result set.
OB: The dataset returns the wrong result or null result set when the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
EB: A relevant error message should pop up when setting an invalid filter expression.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Set the filter expression to 'row[0] equals to 0'.
2. Observe the dataset result.
